1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,280
Characters, actions, places, occupations,

2
00:00:04,280 --> 00:00:09,240
and events in this series are fictional and created for entertainment purposes only.

3
00:00:09,240 --> 00:00:16,400
They are not intended to urge or promote any behavior in the series.

4
00:00:16,680 --> 00:00:17,880
I’m sorry.

5
00:00:17,920 --> 00:00:20,640
I never thought
it would cause a fight between you two.

6
00:00:20,920 --> 00:00:22,880
Why didn’t you tell her
that I’m your girlfriend?

7
00:00:22,880 --> 00:00:23,960
She is clearly hitting on you.

8
00:00:24,240 --> 00:00:26,480
What do I need to do
so that you will work only for me?

9
00:00:26,560 --> 00:00:29,040
Now, I’m at the point where I can choose.

10
00:00:29,080 --> 00:00:29,840
It’s pretty fun.

11
00:00:29,880 --> 00:00:32,280
Did you see the news article?

12
00:00:32,400 --> 00:00:34,480
Yes. But it only tells half of the truth.

13
00:00:34,840 --> 00:00:35,840
Stop blaming yourself.

14
00:00:35,920 --> 00:00:38,840
Everything that happened after that,
it’s not your fault.

15
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:44,560
The view is amazing.

16
00:00:51,200 --> 00:00:52,680
The house is so big.

17
00:00:55,760 --> 00:00:57,280
It’s located right next to the beach.

18
00:00:57,360 --> 00:00:59,360
How much did you spend to buy this house?

19
00:01:00,360 --> 00:01:02,720
Even though I own it,
I barely spend time here.

20
00:01:03,200 --> 00:01:05,880
I only come here once in a while
when I don’t want to see anyone.

21
00:01:07,640 --> 00:01:10,440
I thought you bought this vacation home

22
00:01:10,840 --> 00:01:14,080
to take girls on holiday.

23
00:01:15,560 --> 00:01:16,680
What girls?

24
00:01:17,280 --> 00:01:18,840
You are the first girl I took here.

25
00:01:20,640 --> 00:01:22,160
I want you to know

26
00:01:23,240 --> 00:01:24,840
that you are very important to me.

27
00:01:25,800 --> 00:01:28,520
Among all the girls I’ve been with,

28
00:01:29,240 --> 00:01:31,360
I feel most comfortable when I’m with you.

29
00:01:33,520 --> 00:01:34,880
Is there anything else you want to ask me?

30
00:01:42,400 --> 00:01:43,960
No, I don’t doubt you anymore.

31
00:01:44,759 --> 00:01:45,960
I feel at ease now.

32
00:02:55,200 --> 00:02:57,560
Why didn’t you go somewhere far
for your vacation?

33
00:02:58,000 --> 00:02:59,079
Why did you come to my hostel?

34
00:02:59,400 --> 00:03:01,160
It’s only a 30-minute drive
from your house.

35
00:03:01,400 --> 00:03:03,880
We just want a change of scenery.

36
00:03:04,200 --> 00:03:06,960
Staying in a new place
is already a vacation.

37
00:03:07,200 --> 00:03:09,880
Don’t you know
that we are your big clients?

38
00:03:10,760 --> 00:03:12,560
We are going to stay here for a week.

39
00:03:12,760 --> 00:03:14,320
Oh.

40
00:03:15,920 --> 00:03:17,680
If there’s anything you want,
you can tell me.

41
00:03:17,720 --> 00:03:19,480
I’m here all day, all night.

42
00:03:19,880 --> 00:03:21,600
Ant is going to go to Blossom.

43
00:03:22,360 --> 00:03:23,560
I won’t go there today.

44
00:03:24,040 --> 00:03:24,960
I’ll take a day off.

45
00:03:25,400 --> 00:03:27,079
Prim took days off
to relax with her girlfriend.

46
00:03:27,120 --> 00:03:28,079
I want to do that too.

47
00:03:28,720 --> 00:03:30,560
I have barely taken care of you lately.

48
00:03:30,560 --> 00:03:31,800
Right?

49
00:03:32,560 --> 00:03:34,760
I won’t bother you anymore.
Enjoy your time.

50
00:03:35,560 --> 00:03:37,760
You can take a heavenly ride
as much as you want.

51
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:38,880
Our bed is very strong.

52
00:03:38,920 --> 00:03:40,680
What are you saying?

53
00:03:41,160 --> 00:03:42,240
You are so naughty.

54
00:03:44,160 --> 00:03:44,840
Come on.

55
00:03:46,280 --> 00:03:47,480
I’ll take photos for you.

56
00:04:00,160 --> 00:04:01,880
Airy posted an apology.

57
00:04:03,080 --> 00:04:04,560
Now, people understand what happened.

58
00:04:07,440 --> 00:04:10,280
But I think you should stay away
from social media for the meantime.

59
00:04:10,440 --> 00:04:12,280
People are still digging into your past.

60
00:04:12,760 --> 00:04:16,079
I don’t want you to read anything
that will hurt you.

61
00:04:18,920 --> 00:04:20,040
I’ll try.

62
00:04:22,920 --> 00:04:25,480
I think I’d better turn off my phone.

63
00:04:27,880 --> 00:04:31,280
If there’s anywhere you want to go
or anything you want to do, just tell me.

64
00:04:31,320 --> 00:04:32,480
I’ll take you.

65
00:04:34,159 --> 00:04:35,920
Are you sure
you will have time to do that?

66
00:04:36,320 --> 00:04:38,360
You are a talented director.

67
00:04:38,760 --> 00:04:40,440
You should go to work. I’ll be fine.

68
00:04:40,560 --> 00:04:42,880
I’ve finished all my work.

69
00:04:43,240 --> 00:04:44,760
I’m free to be with you all day.

70
00:04:46,920 --> 00:04:47,480
Really?

71
00:04:47,920 --> 00:04:48,560
Yes.

72
00:04:48,800 --> 00:04:49,960
Is this possible?

73
00:04:50,320 --> 00:04:52,159
A workaholic like you?

74
00:04:53,159 --> 00:04:54,680
That’s the old Prim.

75
00:04:54,880 --> 00:04:56,280
This is the new Prim.

76
00:04:56,560 --> 00:04:57,960
My girlfriend is my priority.

77
00:04:59,800 --> 00:05:00,600
Come here.

78
00:05:02,240 --> 00:05:04,360
I want to hold you all day.

79
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:09,560
Don’t you take care of me too well?

80
00:05:09,880 --> 00:05:10,880
Why?

81
00:05:11,080 --> 00:05:13,360
I’m worried
that something might happen to you.

82
00:05:13,960 --> 00:05:16,440
If something happens to you,
how would I live?

83
00:05:17,800 --> 00:05:21,480
I want to make you smile all day.

84
00:05:22,080 --> 00:05:23,160
I’ll start with this.

85
00:05:24,320 --> 00:05:25,160
Will you smile now?

86
00:05:28,920 --> 00:05:29,760
Are you happy?

87
00:05:32,880 --> 00:05:35,159
Shall we test the bed?

88
00:05:40,880 --> 00:05:44,480
My boss really likes the concept
we discussed in the last meeting.

89
00:05:45,240 --> 00:05:46,560
She keeps praising it.

90
00:05:47,159 --> 00:05:49,560
She is not the type
who likes anything easily.

91
00:05:50,600 --> 00:05:53,280
Thank you for trusting our small company.

92
00:05:53,560 --> 00:05:55,880
Our team is excited about the project
and works hard on it.

93
00:05:57,720 --> 00:06:01,160
But we need to speed up the process.

94
00:06:02,040 --> 00:06:03,520
We want to shoot it next week.

95
00:06:05,160 --> 00:06:06,680
Next week?

96
00:06:12,560 --> 00:06:14,360
Prim is still on her leave next week.

97
00:06:17,800 --> 00:06:21,680
We will find another director
to replace Prim.

98
00:06:22,120 --> 00:06:22,880
Really?

99
00:06:23,240 --> 00:06:27,480
It’s too bad.
My boss really likes Prim’s work.

100
00:06:27,640 --> 00:06:30,280
She wants to work with your company
because of Prim.

101
00:06:30,320 --> 00:06:34,680
She also said she wanted to visit the set
on the shooting day.

102
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:37,280
Min, can you talk to Prim about it?

103
00:06:43,880 --> 00:06:46,680
Sure. I’ll talk to her.

104
00:06:47,480 --> 00:06:49,760
Is the shooting still held in Phuket?

105
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:51,480
Yes.

106
00:07:07,400 --> 00:07:08,040
Ouch.

107
00:07:11,400 --> 00:07:12,360
Are you okay?

108
00:07:16,560 --> 00:07:17,360
Stay here.

109
00:07:17,520 --> 00:07:18,680
I’ll clean it up for you.

110
00:07:30,880 --> 00:07:32,760
Did you get any job interviews?

111
00:07:33,960 --> 00:07:35,080
No.

112
00:07:35,360 --> 00:07:36,960
I sent my resume to many companies.

113
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:38,280
But I didn’t get any calls.

114
00:07:41,640 --> 00:07:43,960
I want to hire you to work here.

115
00:07:44,480 --> 00:07:46,640
But my company is not established yet.

116
00:07:48,080 --> 00:07:50,080
Prim is obsessed with Bambi.

117
00:07:51,560 --> 00:07:52,760
It’s okay.

118
00:07:53,320 --> 00:07:55,040
I don’t want us to work in the same place.

119
00:07:55,440 --> 00:07:57,480
Though I want to be with you 24/7,

120
00:07:57,920 --> 00:08:00,000
I think we need time apart
to miss each other.

121
00:08:01,320 --> 00:08:03,560
When you are tired from work

122
00:08:04,080 --> 00:08:05,560
and want to see your girlfriend.

123
00:08:06,160 --> 00:08:07,640
Then we will hug like this.

124
00:08:16,240 --> 00:08:17,160
I’m sorry.

125
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:19,560
I forgot that we are in your office.

126
00:08:25,440 --> 00:08:26,360
It’s okay.

127
00:08:27,040 --> 00:08:28,680
You can hold me anywhere you want.

128
00:08:29,720 --> 00:08:30,960
I don’t care about it anymore.

129
00:08:34,600 --> 00:08:36,360
We can do more than hugging.

130
00:08:40,919 --> 00:08:41,640
Oh.

131
00:08:42,640 --> 00:08:43,480
Again?

132
00:08:44,320 --> 00:08:45,480
I’m sorry.

133
00:08:47,320 --> 00:08:48,160
It’s okay.

134
00:08:51,280 --> 00:08:52,440
She’s my girlfriend.

135
00:08:53,440 --> 00:08:54,360
What do you want?

136
00:08:55,680 --> 00:08:58,960
Can you get the yellow cup for me?

137
00:09:04,760 --> 00:09:05,480
This one?

138
00:09:06,440 --> 00:09:07,280
Thank you.

139
00:09:32,640 --> 00:09:35,160
Have you ever had a swimsuit photoshoot?

140
00:09:35,840 --> 00:09:36,840
No.

141
00:09:37,120 --> 00:09:38,560
I’m not that confident in my body.

142
00:09:40,440 --> 00:09:41,960
You’re not confident?

143
00:09:42,440 --> 00:09:43,880
Your body is perfect.

144
00:09:45,160 --> 00:09:47,280
I’ve never thought I’m perfect.

145
00:09:47,760 --> 00:09:52,840
When I work, I keep telling myself
that I’m pretty,

146
00:09:53,040 --> 00:09:54,760
I can do it, I’m confident.

147
00:09:55,160 --> 00:09:57,120
If I could choose,
I wouldn’t want to be a model.

148
00:09:57,160 --> 00:09:58,280
I’m thinking about quitting.

149
00:09:58,480 --> 00:09:59,280
Hey.

150
00:09:59,720 --> 00:10:00,960
You can’t quit now.

151
00:10:01,040 --> 00:10:02,360
You are on the rise.

152
00:10:02,400 --> 00:10:03,840
Grab the opportunity while it lasts.

153
00:10:05,120 --> 00:10:06,840
I’m not happy with this job.

154
00:10:07,000 --> 00:10:08,600
There’s no point in continuing to do it.

155
00:10:09,760 --> 00:10:11,640
What are you going to do
after quitting it?

156
00:10:12,000 --> 00:10:13,080
Do you have any plans?

157
00:10:17,680 --> 00:10:22,600
I’ll take a year or two off
to find myself.

158
00:10:22,600 --> 00:10:25,560
I may take a vacation or a class,

159
00:10:27,480 --> 00:10:29,560
or I may just spend time with you all day.

160
00:10:29,600 --> 00:10:31,480
Who would want to spend all day with you?

161
00:10:31,520 --> 00:10:32,440
No.

162
00:10:34,400 --> 00:10:35,360
We just started dating.

163
00:10:35,400 --> 00:10:36,680
Are you already tired of me?

164
00:10:36,760 --> 00:10:40,440
There are things I can do
to make your heart beat fast.

165
00:10:48,840 --> 00:10:49,760
Do you know?

166
00:10:50,040 --> 00:10:51,960
I usually lose interest fast.

167
00:10:52,920 --> 00:10:56,680
But when I find the right one,
I will never let her go.

168
00:10:59,200 --> 00:11:00,080
Do you know what?

169
00:11:00,480 --> 00:11:03,080
When you said cheesy things like this,

170
00:11:03,720 --> 00:11:04,880
I used to cringe.

171
00:11:08,080 --> 00:11:09,360
But now,

172
00:11:10,400 --> 00:11:11,360
it’s not that bad.

173
00:11:12,760 --> 00:11:14,840
Did you change from disliking me…

174
00:11:15,320 --> 00:11:16,160
to loving me?

175
00:11:16,360 --> 00:11:17,360
Love?

176
00:11:17,920 --> 00:11:19,400
Don’t you think it’s too fast?

177
00:11:20,280 --> 00:11:22,280
We should slowly take things
to the next level.

178
00:11:23,200 --> 00:11:25,680
I’ll see it as a challenge.

179
00:11:26,480 --> 00:11:29,880
I will slowly take things
to the next level.

180
00:11:34,640 --> 00:11:36,480
It’s easy for me to like someone,

181
00:11:38,560 --> 00:11:39,760
but hard to love them.

182
00:11:43,960 --> 00:11:44,680
Hey.

183
00:11:46,200 --> 00:11:46,920
Don’t.

184
00:11:48,840 --> 00:11:49,880
Shasha, no.

185
00:11:51,880 --> 00:11:52,840
Get into the water with me.

186
00:11:52,880 --> 00:11:53,640
No.

187
00:12:25,440 --> 00:12:26,320
Careful.

188
00:12:35,560 --> 00:12:36,280
Is it good?

189
00:12:40,640 --> 00:12:41,640
Slowly pour it.

190
00:12:42,720 --> 00:12:43,880
That’s right.

191
00:12:46,280 --> 00:12:46,960
Bambi.

192
00:12:55,000 --> 00:12:57,280
I really liked painting figurines
when I was young.

193
00:12:58,200 --> 00:12:59,960
When my mom took me to a temple festival,

194
00:13:00,360 --> 00:13:02,480
I could spend all night painting it.

195
00:13:03,000 --> 00:13:04,560
I have a large collection of them.

196
00:13:04,760 --> 00:13:05,480
Really?

197
00:13:05,600 --> 00:13:06,160
Yes.

198
00:13:06,200 --> 00:13:07,280
What about this one?

199
00:13:07,560 --> 00:13:09,120
Does it look good enough
for your collection?

200
00:13:10,200 --> 00:13:12,080
Why does yours look so good?

201
00:13:12,800 --> 00:13:14,160
Yours also looks good.

202
00:13:14,480 --> 00:13:16,280
Huh? You are overpraising me.

203
00:13:16,520 --> 00:13:18,160
No, I’m not.

204
00:13:18,480 --> 00:13:20,480
Are you tired? Here.

205
00:13:21,640 --> 00:13:22,760
It’s the last piece.

206
00:13:22,880 --> 00:13:23,640
You can have it.

207
00:13:24,320 --> 00:13:25,080
Hold on.

208
00:13:25,560 --> 00:13:28,520
You always have the last piece.

209
00:13:28,840 --> 00:13:30,080
Especially when it’s a Thai dessert,

210
00:13:30,120 --> 00:13:31,800
There’s no way
you will let me have the last piece.

211
00:13:32,040 --> 00:13:33,760
I saw you want to eat it.

212
00:13:33,920 --> 00:13:34,760
You can have it.

213
00:13:34,800 --> 00:13:35,560
Come on. Eat it.

214
00:13:35,840 --> 00:13:37,360
It said those who have the last piece
will get a pretty partner.

215
00:13:37,400 --> 00:13:39,160
It doesn’t matter to me

216
00:13:39,200 --> 00:13:40,760
because I already have
a pretty girlfriend.

217
00:13:41,120 --> 00:13:41,880
Here.

218
00:13:43,480 --> 00:13:45,080
Where are you going?

219
00:13:46,120 --> 00:13:48,280
I don’t like it when you are doing this.

220
00:13:48,640 --> 00:13:49,760
You don’t like what?

221
00:13:50,400 --> 00:13:52,080
You’re treating me like I’m a patient.

222
00:13:53,240 --> 00:13:55,080
You treat me as if you feel sorry for me,

223
00:13:55,360 --> 00:13:57,120
as if you’re worried
that something might happen to me.

224
00:13:57,160 --> 00:13:58,280
Why are you doing this?

225
00:13:58,680 --> 00:14:00,480
I just want to be a good girlfriend.

226
00:14:01,000 --> 00:14:02,480
You are a good girlfriend.

227
00:14:10,640 --> 00:14:11,400
Fine.

228
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:13,520
What the heck is this?

229
00:14:14,040 --> 00:14:16,440
Bambi, look at the colors you chose.

230
00:14:16,440 --> 00:14:17,920
You have no artistic skills.

231
00:14:18,200 --> 00:14:19,080
It’s terrible.

232
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:23,640
Didn’t you learn about coloring
when you were in elementary school?

233
00:14:23,840 --> 00:14:24,760
I fell asleep in the class.

234
00:14:24,920 --> 00:14:25,760
I was sleepy.

235
00:14:27,040 --> 00:14:28,160
200 baht.

236
00:14:28,400 --> 00:14:29,000
Yes.

237
00:14:29,040 --> 00:14:30,080
I’ll pay it.

238
00:14:35,640 --> 00:14:36,600
200 baht?

239
00:14:40,760 --> 00:14:41,520
Keep the change.

240
00:14:43,000 --> 00:14:43,680
Here.

241
00:14:44,520 --> 00:14:46,160
An artwork from a world-class artist.

242
00:14:46,160 --> 00:14:47,360
Add it to your collection.

243
00:14:55,760 --> 00:14:56,880
Hurry up, Bambi.

244
00:14:57,040 --> 00:14:57,720
What is it?

245
00:14:58,160 --> 00:14:58,960
A mouse?

246
00:14:59,160 --> 00:14:59,680
Yes.

247
00:14:59,680 --> 00:15:00,360
A dog?

248
00:15:00,360 --> 00:15:01,880
A mouse? What is it?

249
00:15:02,320 --> 00:15:03,080
A pig?

250
00:15:03,200 --> 00:15:03,760
Yes.

251
00:15:03,800 --> 00:15:04,720
Yay!

252
00:15:04,760 --> 00:15:05,640
Hurry up.

253
00:15:07,000 --> 00:15:07,960
See? How is it?

254
00:15:09,480 --> 00:15:10,240
It’s big.

255
00:15:10,360 --> 00:15:11,360
An elephant.

256
00:15:13,240 --> 00:15:14,360
You are cheating.

257
00:15:14,440 --> 00:15:15,600
I’m not cheating.

258
00:15:15,600 --> 00:15:17,000
I don’t care. Bambi, good job.

259
00:15:17,000 --> 00:15:19,000
The team that loses will wash the dishes.

260
00:15:21,920 --> 00:15:23,640
A fish?

261
00:15:24,120 --> 00:15:24,840
Starfish?

262
00:15:29,400 --> 00:15:30,160
Five.

263
00:15:30,680 --> 00:15:31,640
Four.

264
00:15:32,040 --> 00:15:32,560
Three.

265
00:15:32,600 --> 00:15:33,240
Chicken?

266
00:15:33,280 --> 00:15:34,760
-Two.
-A chicken pecks a child to death.

267
00:15:35,040 --> 00:15:36,640
Yay!

268
00:15:37,240 --> 00:15:38,360
Don’t get too excited.

269
00:15:39,000 --> 00:15:40,600
Our team’s scores are higher than yours.

270
00:15:40,640 --> 00:15:41,520
You will wash the dishes.

271
00:15:41,800 --> 00:15:42,560
Fine.

272
00:15:42,840 --> 00:15:45,080
I’ll keep my word. I’ve never cheated.

273
00:15:45,120 --> 00:15:46,760
-Okay.
-I’ll wash them.

274
00:15:57,360 --> 00:15:58,080
What’s up?

275
00:15:59,280 --> 00:16:00,160
She’s with me.

276
00:16:02,720 --> 00:16:03,760
Min wants to talk to you.

277
00:16:03,880 --> 00:16:05,000
She said your phone is off.

278
00:16:07,320 --> 00:16:08,480
What is wrong with her?

279
00:16:08,680 --> 00:16:10,560
I already told her
that I would turn my phone off.

280
00:16:13,880 --> 00:16:14,560
Excuse me.

281
00:16:18,760 --> 00:16:20,080
Hello. What’s up?

282
00:16:20,840 --> 00:16:22,680
My throat started to hurt.
Let’s have a drink.

283
00:16:23,640 --> 00:16:25,320
I’ve been calling you all day.
Why didn’t you answer my calls?

284
00:16:25,920 --> 00:16:28,680
I told you that I’m on leave.

285
00:16:29,400 --> 00:16:30,760
But you are the CEO of the company.

286
00:16:30,960 --> 00:16:32,600
You can’t just leave work.

287
00:16:32,960 --> 00:16:35,200
(If we were a big company,
I wouldn’t say anything about it.)

288
00:16:35,240 --> 00:16:36,480
(But our company is a startup.)

289
00:16:36,840 --> 00:16:38,360
I’m sure you can handle it.

290
00:16:38,720 --> 00:16:40,880
This is the reason why we have two CEOs.

291
00:16:41,440 --> 00:16:43,160
Just say what you want to say. I’m busy.

292
00:16:45,200 --> 00:16:46,680
Remember the Phuket project?

293
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:48,840
The client wants to move up the shooting.

294
00:16:49,120 --> 00:16:51,240
They don’t want any director except you.

295
00:16:51,320 --> 00:16:54,360
Why does it have to be now?

296
00:16:54,680 --> 00:16:56,280
Did you negotiate with them?

297
00:16:56,320 --> 00:16:59,360
Yes, but they insisted
that it has to be you.

298
00:17:05,280 --> 00:17:06,440
I can’t do it.

299
00:17:06,480 --> 00:17:08,040
Tell them I won’t take it.

300
00:17:08,319 --> 00:17:09,160
Prim.

301
00:17:09,720 --> 00:17:11,119
I don’t have the right to do this.

302
00:17:11,480 --> 00:17:12,560
You need to do it.

303
00:17:12,680 --> 00:17:14,040
This is a big project.

304
00:17:14,560 --> 00:17:17,640
(If you don’t do it,
we will lose other projects from them.)

305
00:17:18,280 --> 00:17:19,520
(You need to think thoroughly.)

306
00:17:19,920 --> 00:17:23,079
If you go to Phuket for 3-4 days,
you can take a break for a week or two.

307
00:17:23,079 --> 00:17:24,839
(I won’t complain about it.)

308
00:17:24,920 --> 00:17:25,960
(You need to take this job.)

309
00:17:34,520 --> 00:17:35,360
No.

310
00:17:37,320 --> 00:17:38,520
I can’t take it.

311
00:17:38,880 --> 00:17:40,840
(You know what happened to Bambi.)

312
00:17:41,120 --> 00:17:42,360
I can’t leave her.

313
00:17:43,120 --> 00:17:45,520
Tell the client that if they want me,

314
00:17:45,560 --> 00:17:46,640
the shooting will take place
on the original schedule.

315
00:17:46,640 --> 00:17:48,360
If they can’t do that,
then cancel the contract.

316
00:17:48,400 --> 00:17:49,280
I won’t do it.

317
00:17:50,840 --> 00:17:52,360
Hello? Prim?

318
00:17:53,200 --> 00:17:53,880
Prim.

319
00:17:57,400 --> 00:17:58,920
It will happen again.

320
00:17:59,120 --> 00:18:00,480
I think I can do it.

321
00:18:00,480 --> 00:18:03,240
I can handle work and take care of you.

322
00:18:04,200 --> 00:18:05,280
You can stop trying.

323
00:18:08,880 --> 00:18:09,680
Here?

324
00:18:11,480 --> 00:18:12,760
We can do it in the next round.

325
00:18:12,840 --> 00:18:13,720
Here.

326
00:18:17,880 --> 00:18:19,080
What did Min say?

327
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:21,680
It’s nothing.

328
00:18:21,720 --> 00:18:23,560
It’s about work.
We finished discussing it.

329
00:18:23,800 --> 00:18:24,840
Let’s get back to the game.

330
00:18:25,640 --> 00:18:28,440
I’ll let you play.
I can’t play it anymore.

331
00:18:28,480 --> 00:18:29,280
Why?

332
00:18:29,440 --> 00:18:30,560
I have to go to Blossom.

333
00:18:31,080 --> 00:18:32,360
Enjoy the game.

334
00:18:33,520 --> 00:18:34,040
Why?

335
00:18:34,080 --> 00:18:35,320
Didn’t you say you would take a day off?

336
00:18:35,360 --> 00:18:39,600
Fa will be sad
because she will have to sleep alone.

337
00:18:39,640 --> 00:18:41,080
She would want to cuddle with you.

338
00:18:41,120 --> 00:18:44,400
There’s a problem
I need to go in and solve.

339
00:18:44,760 --> 00:18:46,640
Let’s have a drink before you leave.

340
00:18:46,880 --> 00:18:47,960
Drink half of it.

341
00:18:48,480 --> 00:18:49,280
Is that so?

342
00:18:53,080 --> 00:18:56,040
You need to keep my girlfriend company.

343
00:19:02,840 --> 00:19:03,880
It’s alright.

344
00:19:04,240 --> 00:19:06,480
She wants to spend time
with her girlfriend.

345
00:19:06,760 --> 00:19:08,280
You will get new projects.

346
00:19:08,720 --> 00:19:10,280
Let them take some rest.

347
00:19:13,040 --> 00:19:15,760
You’ve been busy with work
since you got here.

348
00:19:16,120 --> 00:19:17,640
You don’t pay attention to me.

349
00:19:18,080 --> 00:19:19,960
I want you to take care of me, too.

350
00:19:22,040 --> 00:19:23,960
I need to solve my work problem first.

351
00:19:24,560 --> 00:19:26,160
I need to talk to Prim.

352
00:19:27,080 --> 00:19:28,560
Hurry up and take care of the problem.

353
00:19:28,920 --> 00:19:32,040
I want to listen to ghost stories with you
before going to bed.

354
00:19:33,280 --> 00:19:35,160
You always get scared
when listening to it.

355
00:19:35,600 --> 00:19:37,160
It helps me fall asleep.

356
00:19:39,400 --> 00:19:41,160
Then you will have to let me hold you.

357
00:19:41,760 --> 00:19:43,480
I will fall asleep easily.

358
00:19:44,240 --> 00:19:45,760
I’ll go to bed with you.

359
00:19:47,120 --> 00:19:49,560
But first, I need to drag Prim
back to work.

360
00:19:50,440 --> 00:19:52,080
Otherwise, I can’t sleep either.

361
00:19:59,200 --> 00:20:00,080
Watch your steps.

362
00:20:01,120 --> 00:20:02,160
What is this?

363
00:20:08,480 --> 00:20:09,360
Surprise.

364
00:20:10,040 --> 00:20:10,880
Wow.

365
00:20:11,720 --> 00:20:13,160
Do you know how to make a surprise?

366
00:20:14,920 --> 00:20:19,360
It’s a basic romantic gesture.

367
00:20:20,680 --> 00:20:21,480
Why?

368
00:20:21,880 --> 00:20:23,960
Star gazing
and wine drinking on the beach.

369
00:20:27,120 --> 00:20:29,680
It’s a good start.

370
00:20:31,800 --> 00:20:32,760
Have a seat.

371
00:20:39,240 --> 00:20:40,440
There are so many stars.

372
00:20:41,360 --> 00:20:43,880
We can see many more stars here
than in Bangkok.

373
00:20:45,080 --> 00:20:46,080
It’s beautiful.

374
00:20:48,520 --> 00:20:49,520
Yes, it is.

375
00:20:50,880 --> 00:20:53,680
It’s even more beautiful
because we watch it together.

376
00:21:00,640 --> 00:21:02,040
I’m thinking

377
00:21:03,400 --> 00:21:05,360
if what you just said is romantic…

378
00:21:06,280 --> 00:21:09,480
or… cheesy.

379
00:21:11,000 --> 00:21:12,880
You always ruin the atmosphere.

380
00:21:13,080 --> 00:21:14,840
I mean it when I say it.

381
00:21:16,360 --> 00:21:17,160
Really?

382
00:21:18,880 --> 00:21:20,280
Okay, okay.

383
00:21:20,560 --> 00:21:21,960
I won’t interrupt you.

384
00:21:22,080 --> 00:21:24,360
If you have anything you want to say,
just say it.

385
00:21:24,400 --> 00:21:28,280
I’m ready to handle
your romantic 101 gestures.

386
00:21:28,960 --> 00:21:31,280
You can make it so sweet
that it will give me diabetes.

387
00:21:48,480 --> 00:21:49,880
I’ll put repellent cream on you.

388
00:21:53,720 --> 00:21:55,160
Are you allergic to mosquito bites?

389
00:21:55,520 --> 00:21:57,240
Have you gotten redness because of them?

390
00:22:05,040 --> 00:22:06,160
What do you want to do?

391
00:22:06,400 --> 00:22:08,000
Do you want to watch the stars
from inside?

392
00:22:08,880 --> 00:22:09,680
No.

393
00:22:09,960 --> 00:22:13,560
I just started to learn
about your Romantic Gestures 101.

394
00:22:23,320 --> 00:22:24,160
Thank you.

395
00:22:28,320 --> 00:22:29,840
I haven’t been in a relationship
for a while.

396
00:22:30,280 --> 00:22:32,560
I forgot this kind of physical closeness.

397
00:22:35,040 --> 00:22:35,800
Hold on.

398
00:22:38,120 --> 00:22:40,960
Are we in a relationship?

399
00:22:43,320 --> 00:22:44,880
What do you think we are?

400
00:22:45,200 --> 00:22:47,040
We are taking care of each other
like this.

401
00:22:47,080 --> 00:22:48,160
Am I still not your girlfriend?

402
00:22:51,000 --> 00:22:52,440
I haven’t asked you yet.

403
00:22:52,600 --> 00:22:53,760
Didn’t get ahead of yourself?

404
00:22:55,360 --> 00:22:56,280
Okay.

405
00:22:56,480 --> 00:22:59,160
We take care of each other,
but I’m not your girlfriend.

406
00:22:59,520 --> 00:23:01,880
Am I just a friend with benefits to you?

407
00:23:02,360 --> 00:23:04,160
Okay. I’ll go back to Bangkok.

408
00:23:12,120 --> 00:23:13,760
I’m about to ask you.

409
00:23:22,000 --> 00:23:23,280
Will you be my girlfriend?

410
00:23:25,200 --> 00:23:27,080
I don’t know what to say.

411
00:23:28,480 --> 00:23:30,160
When I’m with you,

412
00:23:32,000 --> 00:23:33,800
I learn to love myself.

413
00:23:36,680 --> 00:23:37,760
That’s so sweet.

414
00:23:38,360 --> 00:23:39,240
I like it.

415
00:23:42,160 --> 00:23:43,080
So what?

416
00:23:44,360 --> 00:23:45,560
Will you be my girlfriend?

417
00:23:49,760 --> 00:23:50,560
Sure.

418
00:23:51,200 --> 00:23:52,280
What are you waiting for?

419
00:24:12,240 --> 00:24:13,360
You want to do it here?

420
00:24:16,960 --> 00:24:18,480
There’s only us here.

421
00:24:19,120 --> 00:24:20,360
What are you worried about?

422
00:24:43,640 --> 00:24:45,760
You don’t need to wash them. I’ll do it.

423
00:24:46,280 --> 00:24:47,080
Why?

424
00:24:47,240 --> 00:24:49,960
I lost the game. I should wash them.

425
00:24:51,520 --> 00:24:53,160
Do you know how to wash dishes?

426
00:24:55,600 --> 00:24:58,880
I don’t like it when you say this to me.

427
00:24:59,640 --> 00:25:02,040
You are saying like
I don’t know how to do anything.

428
00:25:02,280 --> 00:25:04,760
While I’m trying to change myself.

429
00:25:06,240 --> 00:25:09,240
You don’t need to change yourself.

430
00:25:10,080 --> 00:25:12,560
I like that you are a little princess.

431
00:25:13,600 --> 00:25:15,360
You can be a bit self-centered sometimes.

432
00:25:15,880 --> 00:25:17,360
But I think I can handle it.

433
00:25:18,760 --> 00:25:21,480
You don’t need to give in to me so much.

434
00:25:22,560 --> 00:25:24,680
I want to be a better person

435
00:25:25,240 --> 00:25:28,880
because you always nag me.

436
00:25:31,480 --> 00:25:32,480
You are pretty.

437
00:25:33,080 --> 00:25:34,280
You are cute.

438
00:25:34,600 --> 00:25:35,880
I’ll let you wash the dishes.

439
00:25:36,200 --> 00:25:37,280
You are pouty.

440
00:25:37,920 --> 00:25:39,360
Say it more.

441
00:25:39,680 --> 00:25:40,880
You are my sweetheart.

442
00:25:41,000 --> 00:25:41,920
You are my girlfriend.

443
00:25:41,920 --> 00:25:42,520
Say it more.

444
00:25:42,560 --> 00:25:44,360
Baby, wash the dishes now.

445
00:25:45,720 --> 00:25:46,440
Prim.

446
00:25:49,760 --> 00:25:50,360
Min.

447
00:25:53,640 --> 00:25:54,480
What’s up?

448
00:25:54,600 --> 00:25:56,040
What are you doing here?

449
00:25:57,600 --> 00:25:58,960
I need to talk to you about work.

450
00:25:59,800 --> 00:26:01,080
We have talked about it.

451
00:26:01,760 --> 00:26:03,480
Will you follow me?

452
00:26:04,080 --> 00:26:05,560
Or do you want me to say it here?

453
00:26:09,240 --> 00:26:10,080
I’ll be right back.

454
00:26:10,440 --> 00:26:11,640
You can go wait in the room.

455
00:26:11,640 --> 00:26:12,960
I’ll go talk to Min.

456
00:26:21,320 --> 00:26:22,760
I thought I made myself clear.

457
00:26:22,880 --> 00:26:23,920
I won’t do it.

458
00:26:25,640 --> 00:26:26,680
I understand you.

459
00:26:27,320 --> 00:26:29,160
I know you really love Bambi.

460
00:26:29,560 --> 00:26:31,400
But isn’t Lady Bird also your dream?

461
00:26:31,800 --> 00:26:32,680
Yes, it is.

462
00:26:33,600 --> 00:26:36,080
But the problem happens
because the client wants to reschedule it.

463
00:26:36,120 --> 00:26:38,520
It’s your job to negotiate with them.

464
00:26:39,760 --> 00:26:40,960
I already negotiated with them.

465
00:26:41,440 --> 00:26:42,440
They need to reschedule

466
00:26:42,480 --> 00:26:44,120
because their boss will fly
to watch the shooting.

467
00:26:44,160 --> 00:26:46,160
They even agreed to pay extra
to reschedule it.

468
00:26:47,160 --> 00:26:48,680
I already found an assistant for you.

469
00:26:48,800 --> 00:26:50,760
I arranged everything for you.

470
00:26:50,800 --> 00:26:53,120
All you need to do is go there
and do your job.

471
00:26:53,600 --> 00:26:55,880
Prim, I’ll ask you for only this time.

472
00:26:56,080 --> 00:26:59,600
I’ll talk to other clients to let
other directors work on their projects.

473
00:27:01,720 --> 00:27:05,920
But you know that Bambi broke up with me
because of work before.

474
00:27:07,440 --> 00:27:08,680
I’m sure she will understand it.

475
00:27:09,400 --> 00:27:10,680
Why don’t you talk to her first?

476
00:27:13,560 --> 00:27:14,720
I’ll go talk to her.

477
00:27:14,760 --> 00:27:15,760
Stop.

478
00:27:15,880 --> 00:27:17,960
I’ll take care of it.
You don’t need to do anything.

479
00:27:21,960 --> 00:27:26,040
If the client refuses to reschedule
or use another director,

480
00:27:26,200 --> 00:27:27,400
you should cancel the contract.

481
00:27:27,440 --> 00:27:29,040
I’m sure we will get new projects.

482
00:27:29,360 --> 00:27:30,560
We can’t do that.

483
00:27:32,440 --> 00:27:33,560
How about this?

484
00:27:34,360 --> 00:27:36,160
Why don’t you take Bambi with you?

485
00:27:36,920 --> 00:27:37,960
I’ll take care of it.

486
00:27:38,040 --> 00:27:41,680
She’s not ready to go out to meet anyone.

487
00:27:43,400 --> 00:27:44,560
I think you should leave.

488
00:27:46,760 --> 00:27:48,760
I won’t change my mind. I won’t do it.

489
00:27:49,200 --> 00:27:50,160
Prim.

490
00:27:50,560 --> 00:27:52,880
I’m trying to find solutions for you.

491
00:27:53,080 --> 00:27:54,280
Can you try to work with me?

492
00:27:54,440 --> 00:27:57,760
All this time,
I have never asked for a day off.

493
00:27:58,280 --> 00:27:59,600
I always put our company first.

494
00:27:59,880 --> 00:28:02,280
Can’t I put myself first for once?

495
00:28:09,840 --> 00:28:11,560
You need to get your priorities straight.

496
00:28:11,840 --> 00:28:12,680
Right now,

497
00:28:13,440 --> 00:28:15,480
Bambi is the most important thing to me.

498
00:28:29,560 --> 00:28:30,160
Prim.

499
00:28:30,320 --> 00:28:30,960
Huh?

500
00:28:32,000 --> 00:28:35,560
If you have something you need to do,
you can go and do it.

501
00:28:36,120 --> 00:28:37,360
You don’t need to worry about me.

502
00:28:38,120 --> 00:28:38,960
I’ll be fine.

503
00:28:39,520 --> 00:28:40,960
It’s not about you.

504
00:28:41,840 --> 00:28:43,480
I’m doing this for myself.

505
00:28:44,600 --> 00:28:47,160
I’ve been stressed lately.
I don’t have new ideas for work.

506
00:28:48,280 --> 00:28:49,560
Min will understand me.

507
00:28:50,480 --> 00:28:52,440
I’m sure we can find new clients.

508
00:28:57,240 --> 00:28:59,280
I broke up with you.

509
00:29:01,680 --> 00:29:03,080
Because I thought

510
00:29:04,400 --> 00:29:06,840
I was a burden to your work.

511
00:29:10,360 --> 00:29:12,160
When we got back together,

512
00:29:13,520 --> 00:29:15,760
I thought things were going well.

513
00:29:17,240 --> 00:29:19,560
Things are going well.

514
00:29:20,360 --> 00:29:22,680
I have everything I dream of.

515
00:29:23,760 --> 00:29:25,080
I have you.

516
00:29:39,040 --> 00:29:40,960
You won’t fight with Min over this, right?

517
00:29:45,400 --> 00:29:46,160
No.

518
00:29:48,200 --> 00:29:49,760
Min can handle it.

519
00:29:49,920 --> 00:29:50,880
Don’t worry.

520
00:30:22,480 --> 00:30:24,360
My goal in life is…

521
00:30:26,760 --> 00:30:28,680
to make you happy.

522
00:30:31,920 --> 00:30:33,360
You are doing it right now.

523
00:31:09,280 --> 00:31:13,880
This is our first sex
after we became official.

524
00:31:15,280 --> 00:31:16,840
What about the other ones before this?

525
00:31:18,200 --> 00:31:19,080
No.

526
00:31:19,320 --> 00:31:20,680
I did that to spite someone.

527
00:31:21,440 --> 00:31:23,160
This time, it’s about love.

528
00:31:24,640 --> 00:31:25,360
Hold on.

529
00:31:26,080 --> 00:31:28,200
Did you just say ‘love’?

530
00:31:28,840 --> 00:31:31,360
I’m good at taking things
to the next level.

531
00:31:31,720 --> 00:31:33,960
I’m so talented. It’s been only one night.

532
00:31:34,560 --> 00:31:35,440
No, no, no.

533
00:31:35,680 --> 00:31:39,560
I say that so you will feel encouraged.

534
00:31:40,120 --> 00:31:41,640
I know you are trying.

535
00:31:42,680 --> 00:31:43,880
Stop playing hard to get.

536
00:31:44,320 --> 00:31:45,600
If you love me, just say it.

537
00:31:46,480 --> 00:31:47,880
I also feel the same way.

538
00:31:52,840 --> 00:31:54,680
Shall we go public
when we go back to Bangkok?

539
00:31:56,400 --> 00:31:57,720
Don’t you think it’s too fast?

540
00:31:58,400 --> 00:31:59,640
What about your work?

541
00:32:01,760 --> 00:32:02,880
It’s not too fast.

542
00:32:03,280 --> 00:32:05,160
I told you I don’t care.

543
00:32:05,400 --> 00:32:07,560
I don’t want to work
in the business anymore.

544
00:32:11,000 --> 00:32:13,080
I’m still worried about your career.

545
00:32:13,680 --> 00:32:15,960
You are on the rise right now.

546
00:32:16,320 --> 00:32:17,760
You should seize the opportunities.

547
00:32:18,000 --> 00:32:20,560
You should keep working
until you become a billionaire.

548
00:32:24,160 --> 00:32:26,760
I’ve been living
to please others for too long.

549
00:32:27,120 --> 00:32:28,760
Now, I want to live my own life.

550
00:32:28,960 --> 00:32:31,880
I have a girlfriend,
and I want to show you to everyone.

551
00:32:32,400 --> 00:32:37,160
I want to add the hashtags
‘Shasha belongs only to Gorya’.

552
00:32:38,400 --> 00:32:40,960
‘Shasha loves Gorya.’

553
00:32:42,080 --> 00:32:44,360
‘Shasha has only Gorya.’

554
00:32:44,920 --> 00:32:46,080
Nonsense.

555
00:32:50,560 --> 00:32:54,520
We are like the couple in Notting Hill.

556
00:32:55,120 --> 00:32:55,960
How?

557
00:32:56,840 --> 00:32:59,760
An ordinary person dates a celebrity.

558
00:33:00,960 --> 00:33:02,040
It’s not the same.

559
00:33:02,480 --> 00:33:03,960
You are not an ordinary person.

560
00:33:04,760 --> 00:33:05,960
You are special.

561
00:33:08,920 --> 00:33:09,960
Stop it.

562
00:33:10,280 --> 00:33:11,360
Let’s go to sleep.

563
00:33:12,960 --> 00:33:14,280
Let’s do it another round.

564
00:33:14,360 --> 00:33:15,360
No.

565
00:33:15,880 --> 00:33:16,760
Let’s go to sleep.

566
00:33:17,160 --> 00:33:18,080
Fine.

567
00:33:28,240 --> 00:33:29,360
Are you still using it?

568
00:33:29,760 --> 00:33:31,400
I thought you didn’t use it anymore.

569
00:33:31,840 --> 00:33:32,960
Of course, I’m using it.

570
00:33:33,120 --> 00:33:34,680
I got it from an important person.

571
00:34:12,400 --> 00:34:14,280
I’ve been busy with work.

572
00:34:14,800 --> 00:34:16,280
I barely took a vacation.

573
00:34:16,760 --> 00:34:19,280
This is my first vacation
in the past several months.

574
00:34:20,120 --> 00:34:21,800
We can come here every month.

575
00:34:21,840 --> 00:34:23,080
It’s not that far.

576
00:34:24,760 --> 00:34:25,560
Really?

577
00:34:27,120 --> 00:34:27,800
Deal.

578
00:34:27,840 --> 00:34:29,360
I’ll take my friends too.

579
00:34:30,360 --> 00:34:31,159
Sure.

580
00:34:31,400 --> 00:34:32,679
You are now my girlfriend.

581
00:34:32,719 --> 00:34:34,679
You also have the right to use this house.

582
00:34:36,040 --> 00:34:36,960
Really?

583
00:34:39,199 --> 00:34:40,600
Every bill will be split.

584
00:34:42,080 --> 00:34:43,080
Okay.

585
00:34:43,199 --> 00:34:44,880
If you want anything, just tell me.

586
00:34:45,159 --> 00:34:48,960
I just want us to go to sleep and wake up
to go joking together often.

587
00:34:53,040 --> 00:34:54,080
You’re sweating.

588
00:34:55,719 --> 00:34:56,480
Let’s go.

589
00:35:16,000 --> 00:35:18,160
What do you want to have for breakfast?

590
00:35:21,080 --> 00:35:23,480
Fried eggs and sausages should be enough.

591
00:35:24,400 --> 00:35:26,400
Sure. I can cook it for you.

592
00:35:26,760 --> 00:35:29,160
Cooking is a way to express my love.

593
00:35:30,800 --> 00:35:31,760
Shasha.

594
00:35:36,280 --> 00:35:37,080
Mom.

595
00:36:53,600 --> 00:36:55,520
You woke up quite early, Bambi.

596
00:36:56,520 --> 00:36:58,880
I didn’t get much sleep last night.

597
00:37:00,040 --> 00:37:01,680
Is it because you aren’t used to the place?

598
00:37:01,840 --> 00:37:03,400
Where is Prim? Is she still sleeping?

599
00:37:04,440 --> 00:37:06,680
She’s sleeping soundly.
I don’t want to wake her up.

600
00:37:07,080 --> 00:37:09,480
She must be tired.
She barely takes a vacation.

601
00:37:09,760 --> 00:37:11,960
Ant just got back this morning.

602
00:37:14,280 --> 00:37:16,520
Since we’re dating these workaholics,

603
00:37:16,560 --> 00:37:17,960
we need to understand them.

604
00:37:19,800 --> 00:37:21,520
Are you hungry? I can cook for you.

605
00:37:22,760 --> 00:37:23,760
It’s okay.

606
00:37:24,600 --> 00:37:27,200
Can I have a cup of coffee?

607
00:37:27,760 --> 00:37:28,560
Sure.

608
00:37:28,840 --> 00:37:29,640
Thank you.

609
00:37:39,280 --> 00:37:40,080
Fa.

610
00:37:47,320 --> 00:37:48,000
Fa.

611
00:37:49,080 --> 00:37:49,960
Fa.

612
00:37:51,120 --> 00:37:51,960
Fa.

613
00:37:54,440 --> 00:37:55,280
Fa.

614
00:37:56,360 --> 00:37:57,080
Fa.

615
00:37:59,240 --> 00:37:59,920
Prim.

616
00:38:00,320 --> 00:38:00,960
Prim.

617
00:38:01,520 --> 00:38:02,880
Ant, help me.

618
00:38:03,160 --> 00:38:03,880
Fa.

619
00:38:04,160 --> 00:38:04,880
Fa.

620
00:38:05,800 --> 00:38:06,960
What’s wrong, Bambi?

621
00:38:07,240 --> 00:38:07,920
Ant.

622
00:38:09,840 --> 00:38:10,520
Fa.

623
00:38:10,760 --> 00:38:11,360
Fa.

624
00:38:11,760 --> 00:38:12,680
Fa. Fa.

625
00:38:13,040 --> 00:38:13,640
Fa.

626
00:38:13,800 --> 00:38:14,400
Fa.

627
00:38:14,640 --> 00:38:15,360
Fa.

628
00:38:15,720 --> 00:38:17,120
-Bambi, what’s going on?
-Prim.

629
00:38:17,480 --> 00:38:18,840
Call an ambulance.

630
00:38:19,440 --> 00:38:20,120
Fa.

631
00:38:21,120 --> 00:38:21,800
Fa.

632
00:38:22,000 --> 00:38:22,680
Fa.

633
00:38:27,800 --> 00:38:30,360
Her condition has nothing to worry about.

634
00:38:31,000 --> 00:38:35,360
I suggest you keep an eye on her
not to overdo it.

635
00:38:36,040 --> 00:38:37,560
She needs to take a lot of rest.

636
00:38:38,960 --> 00:38:39,880
Thank you, Doctor.

637
00:38:40,440 --> 00:38:41,240
Excuse me.

638
00:38:49,000 --> 00:38:50,240
Thanks, you guys.

639
00:38:50,840 --> 00:38:52,080
If Bambi didn’t find her

640
00:38:52,800 --> 00:38:55,360
and she got to the hospital late,
her condition could be worse.

641
00:38:56,440 --> 00:38:58,760
Is this the first time
that she passed out?

642
00:39:00,000 --> 00:39:01,160
This is the second time.

643
00:39:02,720 --> 00:39:04,800
The first time happened
while she was working.

644
00:39:05,600 --> 00:39:07,080
Luckily, I was with her.

645
00:39:07,400 --> 00:39:09,080
I’ve been anxious since that day.

646
00:39:10,520 --> 00:39:12,280
What is wrong with her?

647
00:39:27,960 --> 00:39:30,360
She has a leaky heart valve.

648
00:39:31,120 --> 00:39:33,560
She underwent
a heart valve replacement surgery.

649
00:39:35,840 --> 00:39:39,160
The doctor said she might need to undergo
the same surgery again.

650
00:39:42,360 --> 00:39:44,960
This disease cannot be fully treated.

651
00:39:46,080 --> 00:39:49,160
Did she have the condition
before or after dating you?

652
00:39:49,720 --> 00:39:51,960
She has had it
since we were dating the first time.

653
00:39:55,320 --> 00:39:59,280
We broke up because she doesn’t want me
to take care of her.

654
00:40:00,920 --> 00:40:02,160
But I love her.

655
00:40:03,560 --> 00:40:05,640
So I kept asking her to get back together.

656
00:40:07,800 --> 00:40:08,760
You know what?

657
00:40:11,560 --> 00:40:13,960
I barely get
a full night’s sleep these days.

658
00:40:18,280 --> 00:40:19,320
I’m always worried.

659
00:40:20,600 --> 00:40:21,880
If she passes out
or something happens to her,

660
00:40:21,920 --> 00:40:24,840
I won’t be there to take care of her,

661
00:40:26,360 --> 00:40:27,440
I want us to go on a vacation

662
00:40:27,520 --> 00:40:30,160
or trek in the Himalayas,
but I’m afraid to do it.

663
00:40:31,800 --> 00:40:34,080
I’m worried that she might get sick
while we are on a trip.

664
00:40:38,520 --> 00:40:39,560
Deep down,

665
00:40:40,160 --> 00:40:42,360
she probably doesn’t want to be
your burden.

666
00:40:50,280 --> 00:40:52,440
I’ve never seen her as a burden.

667
00:40:55,240 --> 00:40:57,560
In the past, I was not this certain.

668
00:40:59,160 --> 00:41:00,600
But now I can say this.

669
00:41:01,560 --> 00:41:02,760
Without Fa,

670
00:41:03,800 --> 00:41:08,160
I would never have had the courage
to quit my office job…

671
00:41:08,160 --> 00:41:10,760
to open a bar and a hostel.

672
00:41:14,240 --> 00:41:15,760
She gave me a new life.

673
00:41:17,480 --> 00:41:19,160
So I need to take care of her life.

674
00:41:29,560 --> 00:41:31,360
Fa will be alright.

675
00:41:31,720 --> 00:41:34,960
She will get well soon and be able to go
trekking in the Himalayas with you.

676
00:41:35,760 --> 00:41:37,360
Believe me.

677
00:41:38,400 --> 00:41:40,080
She will get well soon.

678
00:41:40,360 --> 00:41:41,360
That’s right.

679
00:41:58,680 --> 00:42:00,360
Why didn’t you tell me that you are back?

680
00:42:02,440 --> 00:42:04,560
I wanted to surprise you.

681
00:42:05,120 --> 00:42:09,360
I’m worried about you
since the Woonsen incident.

682
00:42:10,000 --> 00:42:14,040
I hurried to clear my errands
and flew to see you.

683
00:42:14,840 --> 00:42:16,600
How did you know that I’m here?

684
00:42:17,880 --> 00:42:21,560
I know everything about you.

685
00:42:27,440 --> 00:42:29,160
You don’t need to come to see me.

686
00:42:29,560 --> 00:42:31,240
I have Gorya as my manager.

687
00:42:31,280 --> 00:42:32,480
She is also my girlfriend.

688
00:42:39,120 --> 00:42:41,640
You are both her manager and girlfriend.

689
00:42:42,280 --> 00:42:43,160
That’s great.

690
00:42:43,360 --> 00:42:45,240
Handling two roles alone.

691
00:42:45,600 --> 00:42:46,720
Nice deal, right?

692
00:42:47,760 --> 00:42:49,560
Actually, I’m also her stylist.

693
00:42:49,800 --> 00:42:51,440
I’ve been working in the business.

694
00:42:52,000 --> 00:42:54,160
So I know
what a manager’s responsibilities are.

695
00:42:54,840 --> 00:42:56,560
There is a lot more I need to learn.

696
00:42:57,080 --> 00:42:57,880
Right.

697
00:42:59,520 --> 00:43:03,040
I’m glad you have someone
to take care of you.

698
00:43:03,720 --> 00:43:05,080
I don’t have a problem with it.

699
00:43:05,200 --> 00:43:07,680
You are still young.
It’s normal for you to fall in love.

700
00:43:10,200 --> 00:43:12,960
How long are you going to stay this time?

701
00:43:14,840 --> 00:43:18,280
I’ll stay until I’m sure

702
00:43:18,560 --> 00:43:21,240
that you won’t be taken advantage of again.

703
00:43:22,080 --> 00:43:23,960
If I need to move back permanently,

704
00:43:24,480 --> 00:43:25,760
I can do that.

705
00:43:28,200 --> 00:43:32,160
I want to make up
for our lost time with you.

706
00:43:34,120 --> 00:43:35,960
Let me hug you.

707
00:43:37,800 --> 00:43:39,480
I really miss you.

708
00:43:50,400 --> 00:43:53,360
If you didn’t have a fight with her,
you wouldn’t move in with me, right?

709
00:43:54,640 --> 00:43:55,680
It’s not about that.

710
00:43:56,000 --> 00:43:57,360
The timing is just right.

711
00:43:57,680 --> 00:43:59,200
I want to move in with you.

712
00:44:01,920 --> 00:44:03,960
I saw you kept going back and forth on it
for a while.

713
00:44:04,440 --> 00:44:06,680
I don’t want you to move in with me
because you have a problem.

714
00:44:08,840 --> 00:44:10,440
Now, I’m moving in with you.

715
00:44:11,040 --> 00:44:12,960
You want me to live with you,
and now I’m here.

716
00:44:13,240 --> 00:44:14,840
It doesn’t matter what my reason is.

717
00:44:21,120 --> 00:44:22,160
I’m sorry.

718
00:44:24,920 --> 00:44:26,880
I have a lot of things to worry about.

719
00:44:27,360 --> 00:44:29,560
About my family and my company.

720
00:44:30,640 --> 00:44:32,040
So I’m a bit irritable.

721
00:44:33,160 --> 00:44:34,440
I understand you.

722
00:44:34,920 --> 00:44:37,080
I don’t want to be another thing
that upsets you.

723
00:44:37,680 --> 00:44:39,680
But I think
our relationship is also important.

724
00:44:40,240 --> 00:44:41,360
I know.

725
00:44:42,440 --> 00:44:43,920
I’m trying to balance everything.

726
00:44:46,040 --> 00:44:47,880
I want you to know this.

727
00:44:48,880 --> 00:44:49,920
Right now,

728
00:44:50,920 --> 00:44:53,160
you are the only thing
that can make me smile.

729
00:44:57,320 --> 00:44:59,160
I want to wake up to see you.

730
00:44:59,800 --> 00:45:01,560
I want to come home to see you.

731
00:45:02,040 --> 00:45:04,080
I want to listen to ghost stories
with you.

732
00:45:05,920 --> 00:45:07,560
I really want to live with you.

733
00:45:14,160 --> 00:45:17,280
You need to live
in this small apartment for a while.

734
00:45:17,520 --> 00:45:20,560
Next year, we can get a bigger apartment.

735
00:45:21,480 --> 00:45:23,560
I don’t care
if the apartment is small or big.

736
00:45:24,000 --> 00:45:26,360
When we live together,
I’m sure we will be happy.

737
00:45:28,680 --> 00:45:29,400
Let’s go.

738
00:45:35,200 --> 00:45:37,760
Don’t worry, my mom will leave soon.

739
00:45:38,320 --> 00:45:39,680
She easily gets bored.

740
00:45:39,800 --> 00:45:41,360
She will soon go back to her boyfriend.

741
00:45:42,080 --> 00:45:43,480
I don’t mind it.

742
00:45:43,600 --> 00:45:46,560
This is good.
You will get to spend time with her.

743
00:45:49,480 --> 00:45:51,360
I’ve been living alone for so long.

744
00:45:52,000 --> 00:45:54,000
Now, I don’t want her love anymore.

745
00:45:54,200 --> 00:45:56,040
Don’t say that.

746
00:45:56,760 --> 00:45:58,160
You should give her a chance.

747
00:45:58,680 --> 00:46:00,840
She might feel guilty, like she said.

748
00:46:07,480 --> 00:46:08,360
Thank you.

749
00:46:12,240 --> 00:46:13,000
Shasha.

750
00:46:13,680 --> 00:46:15,400
I can’t find the key
to the bedroom upstairs.

751
00:46:15,400 --> 00:46:16,640
Can you find it for me?

752
00:46:16,680 --> 00:46:18,560
I want to put my bag in the room.

753
00:46:19,800 --> 00:46:21,480
Sure, I’ll go get it.

754
00:46:29,640 --> 00:46:31,480
What do you want to have for breakfast?

755
00:46:31,600 --> 00:46:32,680
I can cook for you.

756
00:46:33,240 --> 00:46:34,080
It’s okay.

757
00:46:34,440 --> 00:46:37,080
I only need a cup of coffee.

758
00:46:39,680 --> 00:46:40,680
So…

759
00:46:41,600 --> 00:46:42,760
How long have you been dating?

760
00:46:44,080 --> 00:46:45,760
Not long. We just started dating.

761
00:46:46,400 --> 00:46:49,720
But we’ve been working together
for a while.

762
00:46:50,760 --> 00:46:53,880
You probably fell in love
because you work closely together.

763
00:46:55,400 --> 00:46:56,200
That’s good.

764
00:46:56,800 --> 00:47:00,280
I’m glad that Sha has someone
to take care of her.

765
00:47:01,960 --> 00:47:03,680
But I have one thing to ask you.

766
00:47:05,440 --> 00:47:06,360
What is it?

767
00:47:08,120 --> 00:47:10,880
I need to be honest with you.

768
00:47:11,960 --> 00:47:15,360
Shasha will be working in the business
for several years.

769
00:47:16,440 --> 00:47:20,960
You know that Shasha’s popularity
is going well.

770
00:47:23,800 --> 00:47:27,240
I don’t want you
to go public with your relationship.

771
00:47:29,960 --> 00:47:32,160
I don’t want to see her popularity drop.

772
00:47:33,520 --> 00:47:36,360
If you really mean well for Shasha,

773
00:47:38,200 --> 00:47:40,960
you know your place, don’t you?

774
00:47:44,520 --> 00:47:47,760
Whatever you do or wherever you are,

775
00:47:48,840 --> 00:47:52,800
I hope that you won’t cause
any trouble for Sha.

776
00:47:56,720 --> 00:47:57,360
Yes.

777
00:47:58,240 --> 00:48:00,080
I know what I need to do.

778
00:48:03,240 --> 00:48:04,080
Good.

779
00:48:04,840 --> 00:48:09,360
We both mean well for Sha, right?

780
00:48:29,440 --> 00:48:31,280
Are you sure
you don’t want to stay a bit longer?

781
00:48:32,440 --> 00:48:33,880
We can stay here for a few days.

782
00:48:35,240 --> 00:48:36,280
Do you want to stay?

783
00:48:37,120 --> 00:48:38,840
If you want to stay, I can stay with you.

784
00:48:39,320 --> 00:48:41,160
If you don’t want to stay, we can go home.

785
00:48:44,320 --> 00:48:45,160
No.

786
00:48:46,000 --> 00:48:47,720
I want to get back to work.

787
00:48:48,120 --> 00:48:50,040
If I rest for too long,
I might lose my passion.

788
00:48:50,760 --> 00:48:53,160
You should get back to work, too.

789
00:48:54,040 --> 00:48:55,640
Go back and sort things out with Min.

790
00:49:02,240 --> 00:49:03,760
Are you okay?

791
00:49:05,800 --> 00:49:07,680
You must be shocked to see Fa unconscious.

792
00:49:11,360 --> 00:49:14,280
A little.

793
00:49:17,400 --> 00:49:20,560
But I’m impressed
by the love between Ant and Fa.

794
00:49:23,520 --> 00:49:26,480
We will take care of each other
like that, too.

795
00:49:30,600 --> 00:49:33,240
But you can’t think the way Ant does.

796
00:49:34,560 --> 00:49:35,360
Think what?

797
00:49:36,440 --> 00:49:39,960
You can’t make all your decisions
based on me.

798
00:49:45,120 --> 00:49:48,560
Sometimes, you need to be selfish.

799
00:49:50,120 --> 00:49:52,200
Don’t love me more than yourself.

800
00:49:52,240 --> 00:49:53,080
Do you get it?

801
00:49:55,480 --> 00:49:56,960
Don’t worry.

802
00:49:57,920 --> 00:49:59,560
I got past that point.

803
00:50:00,120 --> 00:50:02,680
Now I know what I need to do
to balance things in my life.

804
00:50:09,200 --> 00:50:11,000
Don’t be so nice to me.

805
00:50:12,440 --> 00:50:14,360
How would I live without you?

806
00:50:17,240 --> 00:50:19,480
You will never live without me.

807
00:50:19,920 --> 00:50:20,760
Remember that.

808
00:50:30,200 --> 00:50:34,080
Where were we?

809
00:50:35,040 --> 00:50:36,880
You said

810
00:50:37,120 --> 00:50:38,960
you don’t want to be a burden to anyone.

811
00:50:39,880 --> 00:50:40,560
Oh.

812
00:50:45,760 --> 00:50:47,080
I just…

813
00:50:48,840 --> 00:50:50,760
I want to see the person I love happy.

814
00:50:51,440 --> 00:50:52,760
I already found an assistant for you.

815
00:50:53,080 --> 00:50:55,000
I arranged everything for you.

816
00:50:55,040 --> 00:50:56,880
All you need to do is go there
and do your job.

817
00:50:58,520 --> 00:51:02,680
But you know that Bambi broke up with me
because of work before.

818
00:51:09,600 --> 00:51:11,880
I want her to be successful.

819
00:51:15,480 --> 00:51:17,640
I want to be a part of her future.

820
00:51:23,880 --> 00:51:25,760
But why is it so hard, Doctor?

821
00:51:29,280 --> 00:51:31,160
I don’t know if I did something wrong.

822
00:51:32,760 --> 00:51:34,880
It is no one’s fault.

823
00:51:35,360 --> 00:51:38,160
Everyone has their own expectations.

824
00:51:40,200 --> 00:51:41,160
Or…

825
00:51:43,160 --> 00:51:45,160
should I disappear from her life?

826
00:51:49,320 --> 00:51:50,960
So she will have a better life.

827
00:52:03,400 --> 00:52:04,720
Are you really leaving Prim?

828
00:52:04,960 --> 00:52:06,240
She won’t care.

829
00:52:06,360 --> 00:52:08,240
She’s never cared about anyone
except Bambi.

830
00:52:08,600 --> 00:52:12,840
Do you know I’m the reason
why Prim and Min are having a fight?

831
00:52:13,160 --> 00:52:14,400
This is a big event.

832
00:52:14,440 --> 00:52:17,120
You should let someone
with experience do it.

833
00:52:17,120 --> 00:52:18,120
Shall we go public with our relationship?

834
00:52:18,160 --> 00:52:19,680
Your mom will never let us do it.

835
00:52:20,560 --> 00:52:21,920
You got nominated for this award.

836
00:52:21,960 --> 00:52:23,080
It’s because you two
were doing it together.

837
00:52:23,080 --> 00:52:26,720
What about the thing on my bucket list
that you promised to do with me?

838
00:52:26,760 --> 00:52:28,440
Aren’t you going to the last wish together?
